set_params(**params)¶

Set the parameters of this estimator.

The method works on simple estimators as well as on nested objects (such as pipelines). The latter have parameters of the form <component>__<parameter> so that it’s possible to update each component of a nested object.

SR3.math.solvers.fgmres_init(n: int, x: numpy.ndarray = None, b: numpy.ndarray = None) → Tuple[__main__.c_int_Array_128, __main__.c_int_Array_128][source]¶

Load default parameter arrays for MKL sparse linear algebra

The Intel MKL C++ function signature is

void dfgmres_init (const MKL_INT *n , const double *x ,const double *b ,
    MKL_INT *RCI_request , MKL_INT *ipar , double *dpar , double *tmp );

See: Intel MKL Docs

Parameters

  • n – Size of matrix problem.

  • x – Initial estimate of x. Defaults to np.zeros(n).

  • b – Initial estimate of y. Defaults to np.zeros(n).

Returns

MKL parameter arrays ipar, dpar

Return type

(ctypes.c_int*128)(ipar), (ctypes.c_int*128)(dpar)
